k, Benjamin established her own record company and recorded her music independently from Ibrahim. Musical Echoes reflects twenty years of archival research and conversation between this extraordinary jazz singer and the South African musicologist Carol Ann Muller. The narrative of Benjamin's life and times is interspersed with Muller's reflections on the vocalist's story and its implications for jazz history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Okt 2020) 0aJazz singerszSouth AfricavBiography. 0aJazzzSouth Africa. 0aWomen jazz musicianszSouth Africa. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Jazz.2bisacsh1 aBenjamin, Sathima Bea, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311071183740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822393641zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822393641423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822393641.jpg  a978-3-11-071183-7  DUK Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles